snippet: A former Israeli soldier known for his pro-Palestinian activism and radical views, was detained in Egypt, apparently having entered the country without travel documents.
abstract: Andrey Pshenichnikov, former Israeli soldier known for his pro-Palestinian activism, is detained in Egypt after apparently entering country without travel documents; reports indicate that he was trying to reach Gaza through Sinai to fight alongside Palestinians.
lead_paragraph: A former Israeli soldier known for his pro-Palestinian activism and radical views, was detained in Egypt, apparently having entered the country without travel documents.
